Contributing to RecreatorLib

Thanks for wanting to contribute!

By submitting a pull request, issue, or any contribution to this repository you agree to all of the following:

1. You confirm that you are the sole author of your contribution or have the right to grant the license below.
2. You grant the repository owner a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free, transferable, sublicensable license to use, reproduce, modify, distribute, and re-license your contribution as part of the project and in derivative works (see LICENSE).
3. You acknowledge that the Software is released under the Non-Redistributable Source-Available License (NR-SAL) v1.0 and that redistribution of the Software (source or binary) on third-party sites or marketplaces is prohibited except by explicit written permission from the repository owner.

If you cannot accept these terms, do not submit a contribution.

How to contribute
- Fork and create a branch on GitHub, make your changes, and submit a pull request.
- Keep changes focused and include tests where appropriate.
- Follow the coding/style guidelines in the repository.

If you'd like to request permission for redistribution, contact: onlymissanilka@gmail.com
